# WHY A WATERFALL, NOT ONE PROVIDER:
#  - DDG has ~0.2% share in India (Google has ~97%) -> thin coverage of Indian
#    sources, and it's an unofficial scraper that gets rate-limited under any
#    real load.
#  - Serper/SerpApi-style "Google SERP" APIs proxy Google by working around its
#    anti-bot defenses. Google sued SerpApi over exactly that in Dec 2025
#    (DMCA anti-circumvention claims, hearing scheduled May 2026) — the whole
#    category carries live legal risk right now, not just rate-limit risk.
#  - Brave Search API has its own independent index (not Google, not Bing), so
#    it isn't exposed to that specific risk -- but it dropped its perpetual
#    free tier in Feb 2026 (now $5 signup credit, then ~$5/1k queries).
#  - Google's own Custom Search JSON API is fully official (no scraping, no
#    legal exposure) but capped at 100 free queries/day.
# None of these is a silver bullet on its own. The fix is to never depend on
# exactly one of them: try a primary, fail over to the next on error or empty
# results, retry transient failures before giving up on a provider.
#
# Zero-config behavior: with no API keys set, this still runs end-to-end on
